	<body>
	
		<p>Aozan works in 5 steps. It sends emails <b>at each step</b> of the pre-analysis workflow and 
		a <b>QC report</b> at the end of the quality control step.
		The parameters for each step should be writing in Aozan configuration file, 
		an example is <a href="./aozan-example.conf">here.</a>. The available steps are:</p>
		<p/>
		<ul>
			<li><a href="new-run-discovering.xml">New run discovering</a>
               <ul><li>send an email, if a new run is currently running. 
               	For HiSeq Illumina sequencer, send in attachment the first base report</li></ul>
            </li>
			<p/>
			
			<li><a href="end-run-discovering.html">End of run detection</a>
				<ul><li>Checks &quot;<tt>Basecalling_Netcopy_complete.txt</tt>&quot; file creation in the run directory</li>
				  <li>Can handle multiple HiSeq sequencer outputs</li></ul>
			</li>
			<p/>
			
	
			<li><a href="synchronization.html">NAS and mid-term storage synchronization</a>
				<ul><li>Uses rsync</li>
				    <li>Does not copy CIF files (optional)</li></ul>
			</li>
			<p/>
			
			<li><a href="demultiplexing.html">Demultiplexing</a>
				<ul>
                  <li>Demultiplexing is performed by CASAVA/bcl2fastq</li>
				  <li>Parallel computation is done with &quot;<tt>make -j</tt>&quot;</li>
				  <li>CASAVA or bcl2fastq has been modified to provide bzip2 compression functionality (optional)</li>
				  <li>Creates one fastq file by sample</li>
				  <li>Uses alias for samples indexes (optional)</li></ul>
			</li>
			<p/>
			
			<li><p><a href="quality-control.html">Quality control and validation</a></p>
				<ul>
				    <li><a href="qc-global-tests.html">Globals quality tests</a> on general sequencing data</li>
					<li><a href="qc-lanes-tests.html">Lanes quality tests</a> on demultiplexing steps data</li>
					<li><a href="qc-samples-tests.html">Samples quality tests</a> on demultiplexing steps data,
					<a href="http://www.bioinformatics.babraham.ac.uk/projects/fastqc/">FastQC</a> results, and contamination detection results 
                                        (a reimplementation of <a href="http://www.bioinformatics.babraham.ac.uk/projects/fastq_screen/">FastQ Screen</a>)</li>
					<li>Creates a QC report file with thresholds for acceptable values</li>
				</ul>
			</li>
			
		</ul>
	</body>
	
